            <div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
                
                <p n="1">
                    Prosperity! Fortune!
                </p>
                
                <p n="1-4">
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">This<note>That is, the man worshipping a <foreign>liṅga</foreign> represented in the sculpture, which is immediately to the left of the inscription.</note> is</supplied> Tāmaṉ Amalaṉ, lord of Ciṟṟāṭi in Tirunaṟaiyūrnāṭu.
                </p>
                
                <p n="4">
                    Homage to Śiva.<note><hi rend="italic">Pace</hi> <bibl>
                        <ptr target="bib:ARIE1924-1925"/></bibl>, followed by <bibl><ptr target="bib:Kaimal1999_01"/></bibl>, this appears not to be an alias of Tāmaṉ Amalaṉ, but a concluding blessing.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The labelled portrait is portrait 8 in <bibl><ptr target="bib:Kaimal1999_01"/></bibl> (p. 128 and fig. 9).</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="bibliography">
                
